  sodium: 2 g
  serving size: 435
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/soy-and-orange-glazed-pork-wk3-5836b8272e69d7588c7b3962
cuisine: Mediterranean
servings: 2
time required: 40 minutes
---

Preheat your #oven to 200 degrees. Zest the @orange{1} and squeeze the juice into a large #bowl (put the zest in the bowl too), add the @soy sauce{3%tbsp} and the @sugar{1%tsp} and mix together, this is your soy and orange sauce! Put the @pork medallions{4} in the bowl, give everything a stir until your pork is well coated in your sauce. Leave to the side to marinate while you prepare everything else.

Cut the @red onion{1} in half through the root, peel and slice thinly into half moon shapes. Remove the core from the @red pepper{1} and @green pepper{1} and chop into roughly 2cm pieces. Chop the @courgette{1} into 2cm pieces. Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1%bunch}.

Put your pepper and courgette on a #baking tray{} with a glug of @oil{a glug}, sprinkle over a good pinch of @salt{pinch} and a good grind of @black pepper{}. Give the #baking tray{} a shake and pop on the top shelf of your #oven for ~{20-25%minutes}, until cooked and slightly crispy.

Meanwhile, put your onion in a #saucepan on low heat with a drizzle of @oil{a drizzle} and cook for ~{10%minutes} until soft. Add the @balsamic vinegar{1%tbsp} and cook for another ~{10%minutes} on low heat. When your onion is soft and caramelised, put a #lid{} on the #pan, take it off the heat and leave to the side.

Put a #pot of @water{600%ml} on to boil with the @chicken stock pot{1}. Stir to dissolve your stock pot and once boiling add the @couscous{300%g} and a drizzle of @olive oil{a drizzle}. Take the #pot off the heat, put a lid on and leave to the side for your couscous to absorb the stock.

While everything else is cooking, put a #frying pan{} on medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{a drizzle} and lay in your pork. Leave your sauce in the bowl. Fry for ~{7-8%minutes} on each side. > The pork should caramelise slightly but if it starts burning, turn the heat right down. Once your pork is cooked, pop it on a #chopping board{} and cover with foil to rest for a few mins. > The pork is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle. Add your sauce to the pan and simmer for ~{2%minutes}, then remove from the heat.

Fluff up your couscous with a #fork{}, add your veggies, caramelised onion and half your parsley to the pot. Stir everything together. Slice your pork into roughly 1cm thick slices.

Serve your couscous in bowls with your pork on top and a good spoonful of your soy and orange sauce. Sprinkle your remaining parsley over the top. Enjoy!